titleStmt.title: Cambridge, Cambridge University Library, MS Add.2964

respStmt.resp: Edited by Michael Marx in collaboration with Tobias J. Jocham et. al. TEI version created by Yasmin Faghihi and Huw Jones

summary.p: 91 folios; Writing surface: parchment; Shelfmark: MS Add. 2964; Qurʾānic text: Q 18:75-87, Q 18:90-105, Q 18:107-110, Q 19:1-19, Q 19:22-39, Q 19:41-62, Q 19:64-98, Q 20:10-135; 5 Lines per page; Dimensions: 98 x 120mm; Script style: new style I; Estimated date of production: 10th or 11th century AD /4th or 5th century Hijri.

Fragment of an Abbasid Qur'ān probably written in the third or fourth century H. / ninth or tenth century C.E, containing verses 75-87, 90-105, and 107-110 from Sura al-Kahf (سورة الكهف); verses 1-2, 13-19, 22-69, and 73-98 fom Sura Maryam (سورة مريم); and verses 10-28, 35-135 from Sura Ṭā-hā (سورة طه). For more information about the manuscript, see the entry in the Digital Library of Cambridge University.
